                    <span>I hadn't heard of this book until I read a New York TImes Magazine piece by the author, about how he was investigated by the Secret Service while writing the book. The author has a fine sense of humor as he relays the story of how Ballmer became a multibillionaire and possible the highest paid employee in American history. Most important, he researched the story at over fifteen libraries and archives nationwide. There's even a chapter about my town, Birmingha, Michigan, where Ballmer went to high school.</span>
                  
